channel.title: Rune-World Anti-leech fixed
channel.description:
[size=36pt]100% Credits to scape-java for the anti-leech fix, the releaser wanted it removed so just incase, i put it up :) btw its actually shit, so i wouldnt dl it.[/size]
Rune-World anti leech fixed « on: July 02, 2012, 05:37:56 PM » Quote I'm tired of seeing topics about this in the server help section so here .
The so called 'anti - leech' could hardly be considered an anti leech as it was a missing bracket under a break statement on case 13405: and a packaging problem, I have no clue where he got the missing transient variable part from, but there was nothing missing.
The server it's self has all of the original content nothing was touched, the only thing that was modified was the anti leech.
If you get a path not specified error, simply right click the run batch file and change this jdk1.6.0_## to whatever version of java you have. Also, if you're running a 64-bit pc you will need to make a modification to this /Program Files/ You just need to add a (x86) at the end. Enjoy
This doesn't have the client, just the server. http://up.ht/OYxyKO http://uppit.com/vu1tbmd61cjr/Rune-World_Fixed.rar
EDIT: Okay, since I've already got a million pms about the client I uploaded it. http://up.ht/OYOwc1 http://uppit.com/qs11qndvwevt/Rune-World_Client.rar
To change the IP simply go into client class (client.java) and search for the string server = "127.0.0.1".
